---
import ServicePageLayout from '../layouts/ServicePageLayout.astro';

const faqSchemaObject = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much energy do leaky ducts waste?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Leaky ducts can waste 20-30% of your heating and cooling energy, significantly increasing your monthly utility bills."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How is duct sealing done?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "We use mastic sealant and metal tape for permanent seals — not duct tape which degrades over time."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How long does duct sealing last?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Professional duct sealing with proper materials lasts 5-10 years or more with no maintenance needed."
      }
    }
  ]
};
---

<ServicePageLayout
  title="HVAC Duct Sealing in Stanton, CA | Hilo Heating and Air"
  description="Professional duct sealing and ductwork repair services in Stanton, CA. Stop losing conditioned air through leaky ducts with HiLo Heating & Air."
  heroTitle="HVAC Duct Sealing in Stanton, CA"
  heroSubtitle="Your AC kicks on, runs all afternoon, and the house still doesn't feel right? A lot of the time that's air escaping before it even reaches your vents."
  faqSchema={faqSchemaObject}
>
  <section class="pt-4 sm:pt-8 pb-16 sm:pb-24 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 prose prose-lg">
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-brand-blue mt-0 mb-4">Why Leaky Ducts Are Costing You More Than You Think</h2>

      <p>Your AC kicks on, runs all afternoon, and the house still doesn't feel right. Sound familiar? A lot of the time that's not the unit's fault at all — it's air escaping somewhere along the way before it even reaches your vents. HiLo Heating and Air handles duct sealing and <strong>ductwork repair</strong> for homes throughout Stanton, CA and the surrounding Orange County area.</p>

      <h2>What Duct Sealing Actually Fixes</h2>
      <p>Ducts develop gaps over time. Seams loosen, connections shift, sections separate slightly in attics or crawlspaces where nobody's looking. None of it happens overnight. It's slow, and most homeowners don't notice until their energy bill creeps up or one room just won't cool down like the rest of the house.</p>
      <p>Sealing addresses that directly — closing up the small leaks before they turn into bigger <strong>ductwork repair</strong> jobs down the line. It's often the most cost-effective fix available, especially compared to replacing entire duct runs.</p>

      <h2>Why So Many Homes Need This</h2>
      <p>Older houses around here tend to have ductwork that was never properly sealed in the first place, or sealed with tape that's since dried out and peeled away. Tape just doesn't hold up long-term — it's one of the most common things we find when we get into an attic and start tracing duct runs. New construction isn't immune either. Rushed installs happen, and gaps get missed.</p>
      <p>Either way, the result's the same: conditioned air leaking into spaces it was never meant to go, which means your system works harder and your bills climb higher than they should.</p>

      <h2>How We Approach It</h2>
      <p>Every job starts with finding the leaks, not guessing where they might be. We use pressure testing and visual inspection to trace duct runs and pinpoint exactly where air's escaping. Some homes have one or two problem spots. Others have leaks scattered across the whole system, and that usually points to a bigger conversation about <strong>ductwork repair</strong> versus just patching individual sections.</p>
      <p>Once we know what we're dealing with, we seal everything with proper mastic — never tape, since tape is exactly what tends to fail in the first place. Where insulation's been damaged or compressed, we address that too, since insulation and sealing work together to keep your system efficient.</p>

      <h2>What You Get From Getting This Done</h2>
      <p>Properly sealed ductwork means more of your conditioned air actually reaches your living space instead of disappearing into your attic. That translates to lower energy bills, more even temperatures room to room, and less strain on your HVAC equipment overall — which can extend how long it lasts before needing major work.</p>
      <p>It also helps with air quality. Leaky ducts can pull dust, insulation particles, and outside air into your system, and sealing cuts that down significantly.</p>
      <p>With HiLo Heating and Air, you get an honest assessment of whether sealing alone solves the problem or whether you're looking at more extensive <strong>ductwork repair</strong>. Either way, pricing's upfront and the work's backed by our workmanship guarantee.</p>

      <h2>Schedule Your Duct Inspection</h2>
      <p>Stop losing conditioned air — and money — through gaps you can't see. Contact HiLo Heating and Air to schedule an inspection, and we'll tell you straight whether sealing or repair makes sense for your home.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</ServicePageLayout>
